  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0baa\u0bc6\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc2\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc8 \u0bb5\u0bc6\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1 \u0baa\u0bcb\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0bc0\u0ba9\u0bbe \u0bb0\u0bb8\u0bcd\u0baf\u0bbe\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b85\u0bb0\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bca\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0bb3\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bbe\u0bb0 \u0ba8\u0bb2\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc8 \u0baa\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0ba3\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0ba4\u0bc1.",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Despite the allegations, China ignores Russia's political and economic interests.",
      "author": "Rajeeban",
      "body_lines": [
        "Although China has promised Russia, it has not acted in the past few weeks to protect Moscow's interests.",
        "This has disappointed Russian officials, who have said in recent meetings that they want China to ensure unrestricted cooperation.",
        "Russian officials have called on China to maintain new trade commitments ahead of Ukraine's military action and to provide a new form of economic support.",
        "Commenting on the Shangri-La talks on June 12, Chinese Defense Minister Wei Peng said that China had not provided military support to Russia in the conflict with Ukraine, and that its relationship with Russia was not against any third world country.",
        "Meanwhile, in a recent internal study, China's Defense Ministry said that China's full support for Russia could not be based on the sovereignty of Russia over the Ukraine issue.",
        "Lee Hsien Loong has been seen as China's leading Russian affairs expert in recent years.",
        "Meanwhile, on the occasion of the Chinese president's birthday on June 15, the Russian and Chinese presidents held telephone talks.",
        "The statement added that China was ready to contribute to the crisis, adding that all parties should work together to resolve the crisis.",
        "The report also said that China would support Russia on key issues, including security.",
        "Criticism has arisen within China of Xi Jinping's Russian policy on Ukraine. In a recent interview with Hong Kong - based Phoenix TV, leading scholar Yan Soodang noted that China needs skill to ensure that its own interests are not affected by external factors.",
        "The Chinese side has made it clear that only an end to the conflict will allow China greater flexibility in overcoming sanctions and developing trade relations within Russia.",
        "China faces the dilemma of minimizing its own risks and having to help its strategically important ally.",
        "China's predicament highlights fears of secondary sanctions that could cut off technologies important to its own development."
      ],
